374				<span class="op">+</span>
375				<span class="op qw-fast">fast</span>
376				<span class="probe-c">{f(probe.y)}</span>·<span class="cand-c">{f(sel.y)}</span>
377				<span class="op">=</span>
378				<span class="segx-c">{f(sel.px)}</span>
379				<span class="op">+</span>
380				<span class="segy-c">{f(sel.py)}</span>
381				<span class="op">=</span>
382				<span class="score-c">{f1(sel.score)}</span>
383			</span>
384			<span class="strip-note">
385				multiply the matched entries, add the products. The <span class="qw-loud">lilac slice</span>
386				of each bar is its loud product, the <span class="qw-fast">mint slice</span> its fast
387				product; stacked, they are the score.
388			</span>
389		</div>
390	</div>
